1
00:00:53,740 --> 00:00:56,420
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Your Highness, 
the Blacksail Fleet has returned.</font>

2
00:00:56,420 --> 00:00:59,780
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They intercepted a merchant fleet 
from Valencia heading to Wolfheart.</font>

3
00:00:59,780 --> 00:01:02,080
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The haul from this trip is substantial,</font>

4
00:01:02,080 --> 00:01:04,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">enough to arm an entire squad.</font>

5
00:01:04,810 --> 00:01:06,730
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Hmm, not bad.</font>

6
00:01:07,990 --> 00:01:11,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What's the name of the 
Blacksail Fleet's captain again?</font>

7
00:01:11,960 --> 00:01:14,300
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Captain Drake, Your Highness.</font>

8
00:01:19,340 --> 00:01:20,780
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Knight him.</font>

9
00:01:21,430 --> 00:01:25,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Give the Blacksail Fleet all 
the spoils from this raid.</font>

10
00:01:25,390 --> 00:01:28,560
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I believe Sir Drake and all the 
warriors of the Blacksail Fleet</font>

11
00:01:28,560 --> 00:01:31,790
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">will be sincerely grateful for 
your generosity, Your Highness.</font>

12
00:01:32,430 --> 00:01:36,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Also, Kingfisher replied 
that the mission had failed.</font>

13
00:01:36,730 --> 00:01:40,120
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">She said that the pills were 
mixed into the wine and drunk.</font>

14
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:44,070
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">However, Prince Roland only 
slept for a short while, and...</font>

15
00:01:44,070 --> 00:01:45,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Failure is failure.</font>

16
00:01:45,810 --> 00:01:47,170
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I don't want to hear excuses.</font>

17
00:01:47,170 --> 00:01:48,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yes, Your Highness.</font>

18
00:01:49,300 --> 00:01:51,320
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Give her one last chance.</font>

19
00:01:51,320 --> 00:01:53,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Send some of her sister's 
belongings as well.</font>

20
00:01:53,840 --> 00:01:55,880
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Let her act accordingly.</font>

21
00:01:55,880 --> 00:01:56,880
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You may go.</font>

22
00:01:57,390 --> 00:01:59,030
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yes, Your Highness.</font>

23
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:01,600
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">By the way,</font>

24
00:02:02,980 --> 00:02:06,540
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">those pills were provided by 
Alchemy Master Enbis, right?</font>

25
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:09,780
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What did he say at the time?</font>

26
00:02:10,320 --> 00:02:13,310
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">"Dissolves in water. 
Death upon ingestion."</font>

27
00:02:15,420 --> 00:02:16,760
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Hang him.</font>

28
00:05:16,430 --> 00:05:18,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The city wall construction 
is going very smoothly.</font>

29
00:05:18,910 --> 00:05:22,130
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Mr. van Bate guarantees 
it will be completed on time.</font>

30
00:05:22,130 --> 00:05:23,160
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Good.</font>

31
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:24,220
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">How's trade?</font>

32
00:05:24,220 --> 00:05:25,500
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Also going very well.</font>

33
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:28,880
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The food purchased from 
Willow Town arrived at the docks today.</font>

34
00:05:28,880 --> 00:05:31,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The exact quantity is here.</font>

35
00:05:31,470 --> 00:05:35,040
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">As you can see, Your Highness, 
it's enough to see us through the winter.</font>

36
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:35,990
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Good.</font>

37
00:05:35,990 --> 00:05:38,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">After deducting the cost of buying food,</font>

38
00:05:38,140 --> 00:05:39,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">we still have a small surplus.</font>

39
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:41,240
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Um, Your Highness,</font>

40
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:43,230
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">although we have trade income now,</font>

41
00:05:43,230 --> 00:05:46,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">our fiscal deficit remains 
extremely severe.</font>

42
00:05:46,530 --> 00:05:48,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm afraid this isn't 
a long-term solution.</font>

43
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:53,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Currently, our main expenditures are 
all coming from your personal treasury.</font>

44
00:05:53,470 --> 00:05:57,780
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">At this rate, it will only last 
until next spring at most.</font>

45
00:05:57,780 --> 00:05:58,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That's fine.</font>

46
00:05:59,310 --> 00:06:01,500
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It's already very good 
if we can hold out until then.</font>

47
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:04,110
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Besides, we still have the ore trade.</font>

48
00:06:04,610 --> 00:06:08,050
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">As long as we finish building the wall 
and secure our foothold in Border Town,</font>

49
00:06:08,050 --> 00:06:10,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">subsequent ore production 
will be guaranteed.</font>

50
00:06:10,720 --> 00:06:13,860
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm not worried about that, Your Highness.</font>

51
00:06:13,860 --> 00:06:19,700
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Duke Ryan won't let it go if we cut off 
the ore supply to Longsong Stronghold.</font>

52
00:06:19,700 --> 00:06:21,220
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What if...</font>

53
00:06:21,670 --> 00:06:22,480
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Come in.</font>

54
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:28,010
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Your Highness, the Longsong 
Stronghold Ambassador has arrived.</font>

55
00:06:29,400 --> 00:06:34,100
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Barov, you said that the food bought 
from Willow Town already arrived, right?</font>

56
00:06:34,100 --> 00:06:35,920
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yes, Your Highness.</font>

57
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:40,790
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Instruct the kitchen to prepare a 
lavish feast using the delivered food.</font>

58
00:06:40,790 --> 00:06:42,710
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Clean the council chamber.</font>

59
00:06:42,710 --> 00:06:44,010
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I need to host a guest.</font>

60
00:07:06,890 --> 00:07:09,870
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Mr. Hull, please help yourself.</font>

61
00:07:10,510 --> 00:07:13,220
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Ah, thank you, Your Highness.</font>

62
00:07:14,990 --> 00:07:17,680
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Your Highness, what are you holding?</font>

63
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:20,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Oh, you mean these?</font>

64
00:07:20,140 --> 00:07:21,440
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I call them chopsticks.</font>

65
00:07:22,190 --> 00:07:24,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">My people can't afford 
silver knives and forks.</font>

66
00:07:24,660 --> 00:07:27,800
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But these little wooden sticks 
are cheap and hygienic.</font>

67
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:29,700
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The materials are readily available.</font>

68
00:07:29,700 --> 00:07:32,450
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I plan to promote them in Border Town.</font>

69
00:07:33,440 --> 00:07:38,340
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Of course, there's not much 
good food in Border Town right now.</font>

70
00:07:38,340 --> 00:07:40,000
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm afraid you'll have to make do.</font>

71
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:42,880
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Oh no, Your Highness, you're too kind.</font>

72
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:46,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Even at the Stronghold, 
we don't often get meals like this.</font>

73
00:07:47,610 --> 00:07:49,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">This is all to welcome you, of course.</font>

74
00:07:49,740 --> 00:07:51,360
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We don't usually do things like this.</font>

75
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:54,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">All these ingredients arrived 
from Willow Town today.</font>

76
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:57,710
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Willow Town?</font>

77
00:07:58,310 --> 00:07:59,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yes.</font>

78
00:08:00,700 --> 00:08:02,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Please help yourself, Mr. Hull.</font>

79
00:08:02,350 --> 00:08:03,700
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Don't hold back.</font>

80
00:08:03,700 --> 00:08:05,730
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We can discuss business after we eat.</font>

81
00:08:14,130 --> 00:08:16,400
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Thank you for your hospitality, 
Your Highness.</font>

82
00:08:17,180 --> 00:08:20,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm here on behalf of Longsong 
Stronghold to inform you that</font>

83
00:08:21,020 --> 00:08:23,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">the deadline for the 
ore delivery has passed.</font>

84
00:08:23,530 --> 00:08:27,180
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The Stronghold has already prepared 
the food to be sent to Border Town.</font>

85
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,100
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But...</font>

86
00:08:30,320 --> 00:08:32,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We have yet to receive the ore.</font>

87
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:34,960
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The thing is,</font>

88
00:08:34,960 --> 00:08:38,190
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">an unfortunate incident occurred recently.</font>

89
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:41,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The northern mine collapsed,</font>

90
00:08:41,250 --> 00:08:43,210
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and production stopped for a long time.</font>

91
00:08:43,700 --> 00:08:45,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Oops, they fell.</font>

92
00:08:48,070 --> 00:08:50,930
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Basically, we can't produce 
the agreed quantity of ore.</font>

93
00:08:50,930 --> 00:08:53,190
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We only have about two 
months' worth of production.</font>

94
00:08:53,190 --> 00:08:54,880
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I heard about the mine's situation.</font>

95
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:58,460
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Well then... why not deliver 
two months' worth for now?</font>

96
00:08:58,460 --> 00:09:01,120
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The food I'd get in return 
for two months' worth of ore</font>

97
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:02,930
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">wouldn't be enough to feed my people.</font>

98
00:09:04,650 --> 00:09:09,070
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Two years ago, many people in Border Town 
starved to death due to food shortages.</font>

99
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:12,280
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I will not allow that to happen again.</font>

100
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:16,640
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">This practice of bartering 
with the Stronghold...</font>

101
00:09:17,930 --> 00:09:19,930
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">must be abolished.</font>

102
00:09:20,520 --> 00:09:23,200
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Ah, Your Highness, you mean...</font>

103
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:24,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">To be honest with you,</font>

104
00:09:24,530 --> 00:09:27,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I have already sold 
the ore to Willow Town,</font>

105
00:09:27,020 --> 00:09:30,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and bought enough food from them 
to last through the winter.</font>

106
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:33,430
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Not only were they willing to 
buy the ore with gold royals,</font>

107
00:09:33,430 --> 00:09:36,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">but were also prepared to sell 
various goods at market prices.</font>

108
00:09:36,720 --> 00:09:39,820
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Anything that can be bought 
with money, they sell.</font>

109
00:09:39,820 --> 00:09:40,830
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">So...</font>

110
00:09:41,430 --> 00:09:44,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Trading with Willow Town is 
more advantageous for Border Town.</font>

111
00:09:48,140 --> 00:09:49,500
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They fell again.</font>

112
00:09:50,300 --> 00:09:55,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">So... that explains the ships 
from Willow Town at the dock.</font>

113
00:10:05,550 --> 00:10:08,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Your Highness, 
I understand your reasoning now.</font>

114
00:10:09,040 --> 00:10:11,690
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But it seems there are 
a few problems with this.</font>

115
00:10:11,690 --> 00:10:13,700
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Oh? Please elaborate.</font>

116
00:10:13,700 --> 00:10:17,200
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">To my knowledge, Willow Town 
has never traded in ore before.</font>

117
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:19,070
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Even if they pay in currency,</font>

118
00:10:19,070 --> 00:10:20,950
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">the price wouldn't be high.</font>

119
00:10:20,950 --> 00:10:25,170
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I think, at most, it would 
be half the market price.</font>

120
00:10:25,170 --> 00:10:27,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">For you, that would be a loss.</font>

121
00:10:27,140 --> 00:10:28,870
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It won't be sustainable.</font>

122
00:10:28,870 --> 00:10:30,550
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Trade is determined by the market.</font>

123
00:10:30,550 --> 00:10:33,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Longsong Stronghold has operated in 
the Western Region for over a century.</font>

124
00:10:33,270 --> 00:10:34,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Only a fortress on our scale</font>

125
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:37,150
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">has the capacity to consume so much ore.</font>

126
00:10:37,150 --> 00:10:40,220
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The Stronghold far surpasses Willow Town,</font>

127
00:10:40,220 --> 00:10:42,420
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">both in development 
prospects and market size.</font>

128
00:10:42,420 --> 00:10:43,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">So, in the long term,</font>

129
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:46,220
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Border Town's primary trading partner 
should be the Stronghold,</font>

130
00:10:46,220 --> 00:10:48,940
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">as that would better serve 
the interests of both parties.</font>

131
00:10:53,620 --> 00:10:54,640
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Thirty percent.</font>

132
00:10:55,220 --> 00:10:59,180
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">If the Stronghold can purchase 
ore at 30% below market price,</font>

133
00:10:59,180 --> 00:11:00,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">then it'd be a win-win situation.</font>

134
00:11:03,490 --> 00:11:08,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I've long heard that Petrov Hull of the 
Honeysuckle family is a skilled merchant.</font>

135
00:11:08,740 --> 00:11:10,400
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Your reputation is well-deserved.</font>

136
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:13,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Thank you for your compliment, 
Your Highness.</font>

137
00:11:13,660 --> 00:11:15,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Based on the terms you just proposed,</font>

138
00:11:15,740 --> 00:11:18,240
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">it would indeed create 
a win-win situation.</font>

139
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:19,520
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">However...</font>

140
00:11:20,050 --> 00:11:21,590
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Can you guarantee that this will be</font>

141
00:11:21,590 --> 00:11:24,150
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">the unanimous decision of 
the Stronghold's Six Families?</font>

142
00:11:24,150 --> 00:11:25,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Well...</font>

143
00:11:25,890 --> 00:11:27,410
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I can't guarantee it 100%,</font>

144
00:11:28,210 --> 00:11:30,870
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">but I manage all of the 
Stronghold's foreign trade.</font>

145
00:11:30,870 --> 00:11:33,520
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I will do my best to convince 
the Duke and the Six Families</font>

146
00:11:33,520 --> 00:11:35,630
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">to accept this mutually 
beneficial outcome.</font>

147
00:11:39,490 --> 00:11:41,950
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I will return to the Stronghold 
to draft a new contract</font>

148
00:11:41,950 --> 00:11:44,010
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">before visiting Your Highness again.</font>

149
00:11:44,010 --> 00:11:47,520
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Good. Then I shall await 
your good news, Ambassador.</font>

150
00:11:53,520 --> 00:11:54,310
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Your Highness,</font>

151
00:11:55,090 --> 00:11:56,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">there is one more thing.</font>

152
00:11:56,660 --> 00:11:58,680
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">There are only two months 
left until winter.</font>

153
00:11:58,680 --> 00:12:00,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Willow Town is quite far away.</font>

154
00:12:01,980 --> 00:12:05,820
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The journey can be dangerous.</font>

155
00:12:06,770 --> 00:12:10,710
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Therefore, I strongly advise you to 
consider certain practical matters,</font>

156
00:12:11,830 --> 00:12:14,520
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">from Duke Ryan's perspective.</font>

157
00:12:15,010 --> 00:12:16,880
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You misunderstand, Mr. Hull.</font>

158
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:19,520
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I never planned for my people to 
spend the winter in Willow Town.</font>

159
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:22,110
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Then you mean...</font>

160
00:12:22,110 --> 00:12:23,940
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Nor do I plan to go to 
Longsong Stronghold.</font>

161
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:26,340
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We're not going anywhere.</font>

162
00:12:26,340 --> 00:12:30,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">This winter, I will build a city 
wall to defend Border Town,</font>

163
00:12:33,670 --> 00:12:37,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">making it the new border of 
the Kingdom of Graycastle.</font>

164
00:12:40,930 --> 00:12:42,400
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I understand.</font>

165
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:44,490
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But, Your Highness, 
let me say one last thing.</font>

166
00:12:44,490 --> 00:12:47,690
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Your decision affects the fate 
of everyone in Border Town.</font>

167
00:12:47,690 --> 00:12:50,090
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">If anything goes wrong, 
you have a way out,</font>

168
00:12:50,700 --> 00:12:51,750
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">but they do not.</font>

169
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:53,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Thank you for your concern, Ambassador.</font>

170
00:12:53,570 --> 00:12:56,060
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I am fully aware of 
what my decision means.</font>

171
00:12:56,060 --> 00:12:59,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Very well. I have noted 
all your conditions.</font>

172
00:13:16,550 --> 00:13:17,480
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Barov,</font>

173
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:20,620
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">prepare the food as planned.</font>

174
00:13:20,620 --> 00:13:22,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yes, Your Highness.</font>

175
00:13:28,060 --> 00:13:29,050
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Oh?</font>

176
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:32,060
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What else did that kid say?</font>

177
00:13:32,060 --> 00:13:34,670
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">His Highness said he has 
already sold the existing ore</font>

178
00:13:34,670 --> 00:13:37,220
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">to Willow Town in exchange for currency.</font>

179
00:13:38,240 --> 00:13:39,310
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Also,</font>

180
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:43,760
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">he has bought enough food for the entire 
town this winter from Willow Town.</font>

181
00:13:44,310 --> 00:13:46,060
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">He did what?</font>

182
00:13:46,060 --> 00:13:47,750
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What does this mean?</font>

183
00:13:47,750 --> 00:13:48,560
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yeah...</font>

184
00:13:49,680 --> 00:13:51,060
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Anything else?</font>

185
00:13:51,510 --> 00:13:54,010
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Also, Prince Roland said that</font>

186
00:13:54,010 --> 00:13:55,480
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">during this year's Months of Demons,</font>

187
00:13:55,480 --> 00:13:57,260
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">he won't be seeking refuge 
at the Stronghold.</font>

188
00:13:57,260 --> 00:13:58,880
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The people won't leave either.</font>

189
00:13:58,880 --> 00:14:01,420
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">His Highness is building a 
city wall in Border Town.</font>

190
00:14:01,420 --> 00:14:03,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">He also said...</font>

191
00:14:03,660 --> 00:14:05,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What else did he say?</font>

192
00:14:05,140 --> 00:14:08,360
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">He also said that he will lead his 
people to defeat the demonic beasts</font>

193
00:14:08,360 --> 00:14:09,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and protect Border Town,</font>

194
00:14:09,390 --> 00:14:14,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">making it the new border of 
the Kingdom of Graycastle.</font>

195
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:19,110
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What does he think this place is?</font>

196
00:14:19,110 --> 00:14:20,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Graycastle?</font>

197
00:14:20,820 --> 00:14:22,930
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">His Highness doesn't think 
building a city wall</font>

198
00:14:22,930 --> 00:14:24,960
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">is the same as playing house, does he?</font>

199
00:14:24,960 --> 00:14:28,320
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Piling up a few broken rocks 
and slapping on some wet mud?</font>

200
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:30,480
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">If he built it a bit higher,</font>

201
00:14:30,480 --> 00:14:32,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">it would collapse immediately.</font>

202
00:14:33,520 --> 00:14:37,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Your Grace, the Prince is bluffing!</font>

203
00:14:37,250 --> 00:14:40,000
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Petrov is timid and got tricked by him.</font>

204
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,460
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We can't fall for it.</font>

205
00:14:41,460 --> 00:14:42,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But it's not a bad thing.</font>

206
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:45,850
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">If he fails and flees back 
to Longsong Stronghold,</font>

207
00:14:45,850 --> 00:14:47,860
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">he'll naturally be at our mercy.</font>

208
00:14:47,860 --> 00:14:49,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And if he dies over there...</font>

209
00:14:49,770 --> 00:14:51,400
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The farce ends,</font>

210
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:53,520
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and all's well that ends well.</font>

211
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:54,670
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Boris.</font>

212
00:14:55,190 --> 00:14:57,600
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yes, Your Grace?</font>

213
00:14:57,600 --> 00:15:00,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What do you know about the city wall?</font>

214
00:15:00,770 --> 00:15:03,600
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Well, Your Grace, a while back,</font>

215
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:06,450
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">that kid was indeed recruiting 
stonemasons and workers.</font>

216
00:15:06,450 --> 00:15:08,420
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But I thought...</font>

217
00:15:08,420 --> 00:15:11,280
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I thought he was just renovating 
his garden or something.</font>

218
00:15:11,280 --> 00:15:13,780
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I didn't hear anything about a city wall.</font>

219
00:15:21,660 --> 00:15:26,170
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Petrov, did you see that city wall?</font>

220
00:15:26,170 --> 00:15:29,200
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Before leaving Border Town, 
I specifically went to check.</font>

221
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:32,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">On the edge of the Misty Forest, 
there were indeed people building a wall.</font>

222
00:15:33,020 --> 00:15:34,780
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I don't know what method 
the Prince is using,</font>

223
00:15:34,780 --> 00:15:36,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">but construction is proceeding rapidly.</font>

224
00:15:36,470 --> 00:15:38,640
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">However, the wall isn't very large.</font>

225
00:15:38,640 --> 00:15:42,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">In my opinion, it would be difficult 
to resist the demonic beasts.</font>

226
00:15:42,560 --> 00:15:44,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What do you think we should do?</font>

227
00:16:53,110 --> 00:16:54,670
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Residents of Border Town!</font>

228
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:59,420
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I am Roland Wimbledon, the Fourth Prince 
of the Kingdom of Graycastle.</font>

229
00:16:59,420 --> 00:17:01,120
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I have gathered you here today</font>

230
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:04,080
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">because there is an important 
matter I must tell you.</font>

231
00:17:04,620 --> 00:17:06,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Earlier this morning,</font>

232
00:17:06,350 --> 00:17:09,600
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">the Longsong Stronghold ambassador 
arrived in Border Town.</font>

233
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:11,820
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">He came for the ore delivery.</font>

234
00:17:12,720 --> 00:17:15,360
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">As you all know, a month ago,</font>

235
00:17:15,360 --> 00:17:17,600
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">we suffered an unfortunate accident.</font>

236
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:20,110
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The North Slope Mine collapsed,</font>

237
00:17:20,110 --> 00:17:23,790
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and to this day, mining operations 
have not fully resumed.</font>

238
00:17:23,790 --> 00:17:26,630
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We cannot produce enough ore.</font>

239
00:17:26,630 --> 00:17:28,460
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I explained the situation 
to the ambassador,</font>

240
00:17:28,460 --> 00:17:30,190
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">hoping he would make an exception</font>

241
00:17:30,190 --> 00:17:33,050
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and give us our winter 
allocation of food in full.</font>

242
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:35,980
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">However, he refused.</font>

243
00:17:35,980 --> 00:17:38,510
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">There was no room for negotiation.</font>

244
00:17:38,510 --> 00:17:41,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">He refused to give us our full 
allocation of food, just like</font>

245
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:44,600
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">during the Months of Demons two years ago.</font>

246
00:17:45,570 --> 00:17:49,490
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And what's worse, the Graycastle 
astrologers have told me that</font>

247
00:17:49,490 --> 00:17:52,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">this winter will be longer than usual.</font>

248
00:17:52,390 --> 00:17:56,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The Months of Demons could last 
for more than four months.</font>

249
00:17:56,250 --> 00:17:59,900
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That means, if we let things 
proceed as they are,</font>

250
00:17:59,900 --> 00:18:02,360
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">the tragedy of two years 
ago will repeat itself,</font>

251
00:18:02,360 --> 00:18:04,010
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">perhaps even worse.</font>

252
00:18:04,750 --> 00:18:06,560
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Everyone, please remember.</font>

253
00:18:06,560 --> 00:18:10,600
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Please remember what 
we lost two years ago.</font>

254
00:18:11,140 --> 00:18:14,230
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Some of us lost friends,</font>

255
00:18:14,230 --> 00:18:15,600
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">some lost loved ones,</font>

256
00:18:16,180 --> 00:18:18,100
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and some lost children.</font>

257
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:19,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">This time...</font>

258
00:18:20,460 --> 00:18:22,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What more will we have to lose?</font>

259
00:18:23,100 --> 00:18:26,320
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What more <i>do</i> we have left to lose?</font>

260
00:18:29,310 --> 00:18:33,080
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I believe the Prince's move with the 
city wall is ultimately about trade.</font>

261
00:18:33,660 --> 00:18:35,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">His strategy is to advance by retreating.</font>

262
00:18:35,250 --> 00:18:39,520
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">His ultimate goal is probably to force us 
to trade with Border Town using currency.</font>

263
00:18:39,520 --> 00:18:43,120
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Prince Roland was sent to govern 
Border Town due to the Royal Decree,</font>

264
00:18:43,120 --> 00:18:44,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">so these actions make sense.</font>

265
00:18:45,630 --> 00:18:48,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Also, there's no need for a direct 
conflict with the Graycastle royal family.</font>

266
00:18:49,230 --> 00:18:51,330
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">If we can fulfill His Highness's request,</font>

267
00:18:51,330 --> 00:18:54,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and purchase ore at 30% below 
market price from now on,</font>

268
00:18:54,250 --> 00:18:56,340
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">it would still be a worthwhile deal.</font>

269
00:18:56,340 --> 00:18:59,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Furthermore, if he truly 
can hold Border Town,</font>

270
00:18:59,350 --> 00:19:00,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">it benefits us as well.</font>

271
00:19:00,770 --> 00:19:04,640
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">First, we can save the enormous expense 
of fighting the demonic beasts.</font>

272
00:19:04,640 --> 00:19:07,940
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Second, the vast lands between 
the Stronghold and Border Town</font>

273
00:19:07,940 --> 00:19:09,850
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">could be cultivated and utilized.</font>

274
00:19:09,850 --> 00:19:11,760
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">This is all your territory.</font>

275
00:19:11,760 --> 00:19:15,080
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Finally, Prince Roland 
won't stay here forever.</font>

276
00:19:15,080 --> 00:19:16,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The Royal Decree lasts only five years.</font>

277
00:19:16,770 --> 00:19:19,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">In five years, we will have a 
more prosperous Border Town.</font>

278
00:19:19,810 --> 00:19:22,590
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The people there will 
still be your subjects.</font>

279
00:19:22,590 --> 00:19:26,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">By then, you'll have the third largest 
territory in the entire Kingdom.</font>

280
00:19:26,470 --> 00:19:27,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">So my suggestion is that</font>

281
00:19:28,420 --> 00:19:31,400
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">we should, from now on, 
purchase ore at 30% below market price.</font>

282
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:33,460
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Also, send people to help the 
Fourth Prince build the wall,</font>

283
00:19:33,460 --> 00:19:35,160
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and resist the demonic beasts together.</font>

284
00:19:36,090 --> 00:19:38,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Hah! Petrov, you're being far too naive!</font>

285
00:19:39,470 --> 00:19:40,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Are you joking?</font>

286
00:19:45,840 --> 00:19:47,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Interesting.</font>

287
00:19:47,770 --> 00:19:52,380
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">According to you, this must be another 
so-called "win-win" conclusion, right?</font>

288
00:19:53,940 --> 00:19:54,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yes.</font>

289
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:58,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The idea isn't bad.</font>

290
00:19:59,030 --> 00:20:02,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But ultimately, it's still 
a merchant's perspective.</font>

291
00:20:02,270 --> 00:20:06,090
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Merchants only see gains 
and losses, but...</font>

292
00:20:06,610 --> 00:20:08,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Petrov...</font>

293
00:20:08,900 --> 00:20:13,210
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I didn't get to my current position 
by only considering profits.</font>

294
00:20:13,210 --> 00:20:16,770
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Why would I do business with 
someone I can't control?</font>

295
00:20:17,970 --> 00:20:22,410
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Under my rule, disobey me, 
and you will be punished.</font>

296
00:20:22,410 --> 00:20:26,420
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">As for Border Town, whether it 
prospers or decays is unimportant.</font>

297
00:20:26,420 --> 00:20:29,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What matters is that it's my territory.</font>

298
00:20:29,570 --> 00:20:31,510
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">No one else gets to interfere,</font>

299
00:20:32,090 --> 00:20:34,300
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">not even a Prince.</font>

300
00:20:35,280 --> 00:20:38,750
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Everyone, look! This is the food for 
winter I purchased from Willow Town.</font>

301
00:20:38,750 --> 00:20:41,600
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It arrived in Border Town 
earlier this morning.</font>

302
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:44,980
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">There's bread, cheese, 
mead, and dried meat,</font>

303
00:20:44,980 --> 00:20:46,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">enough for the entire winter.</font>

304
00:20:46,570 --> 00:20:48,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Everyone will be fed.</font>

305
00:20:48,270 --> 00:20:50,590
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I swear in the name of Wimbledon:</font>

306
00:20:50,590 --> 00:20:53,440
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I won't allow the tragedy of 
two years ago to repeat itself.</font>

307
00:20:53,440 --> 00:20:55,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Thank you, Your Highness!</font>

308
00:20:55,270 --> 00:20:58,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Long live the Prince!</font>

309
00:20:58,720 --> 00:20:59,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">However!</font>

310
00:21:00,680 --> 00:21:04,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">By doing this, we have essentially 
offended Longsong Stronghold.</font>

311
00:21:04,350 --> 00:21:08,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They've threatened to stop providing 
shelter for everyone this winter.</font>

312
00:21:08,270 --> 00:21:11,680
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I told them that we're not 
going anywhere this winter.</font>

313
00:21:11,680 --> 00:21:13,440
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We'll stay in our homeland,</font>

314
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:15,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and spend the winter in Border Town.</font>

315
00:21:16,270 --> 00:21:18,230
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Some of you may have already seen it.</font>

316
00:21:18,230 --> 00:21:19,600
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">To the west of Border Town,</font>

317
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:22,800
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">a sturdy city wall is 
steadily being built.</font>

318
00:21:22,800 --> 00:21:26,460
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I know some worry whether we can 
withstand the demonic beasts' onslaught.</font>

319
00:21:26,460 --> 00:21:28,190
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But let me tell you this:</font>

320
00:21:28,190 --> 00:21:31,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">demonic beasts are no stronger 
than ordinary wild animals.</font>

321
00:21:31,530 --> 00:21:33,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Though they have thick 
hides and tough flesh,</font>

322
00:21:33,570 --> 00:21:36,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">they can't climb walls, 
and they can't bite through stone.</font>

323
00:21:36,390 --> 00:21:38,490
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They're nothing but pitiful targets.</font>

324
00:21:39,610 --> 00:21:44,210
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I, Roland Wimbledon, Fourth Prince 
of the Kingdom of Graycastle,</font>

325
00:21:44,210 --> 00:21:46,890
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">hereby issue an urgent call to action.</font>

326
00:21:46,890 --> 00:21:48,860
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">All those who can take up arms,</font>

327
00:21:48,860 --> 00:21:50,620
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">in order to defend our homeland,</font>

328
00:21:50,620 --> 00:21:52,820
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">in order to let us live with dignity,</font>

329
00:21:52,820 --> 00:21:55,440
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">pick up your weapons and join the militia!</font>

330
00:21:55,440 --> 00:21:59,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">All militia members will receive 
25 silver royals every month.</font>

331
00:21:59,270 --> 00:22:01,230
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">If someone unfortunately falls in battle,</font>

332
00:22:01,230 --> 00:22:05,150
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">their family will receive five 
gold royals as compensation.</font>

333
00:22:05,150 --> 00:22:08,590
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Tell me, would you rather hide in 
the shacks of Longsong Stronghold,</font>

334
00:22:08,590 --> 00:22:11,360
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">pathetically starve to death, 
and freeze to death without dignity?</font>

335
00:22:11,360 --> 00:22:14,820
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Or would you rather follow me and 
protect your friends and family,</font>

336
00:22:14,820 --> 00:22:17,390
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">defend Border Town, 
and defend your homeland</font>

337
00:22:17,390 --> 00:22:19,220
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">until the final moment?!</font>

338
00:22:19,220 --> 00:22:22,040
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Defend Border Town!</font>

339
00:22:30,860 --> 00:22:34,970
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You just said the air around us is 
made up of many different kinds of gases.</font>

340
00:22:34,970 --> 00:22:35,790
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Is that true?</font>

341
00:22:35,790 --> 00:22:38,430
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Of course. Even though 
they all look the same.</font>

342
00:22:38,430 --> 00:22:40,790
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Your Highness, I don't understand.</font>

343
00:22:40,790 --> 00:22:42,240
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">If they all look the same,</font>

344
00:22:42,240 --> 00:22:44,230
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">how do you know there are different gases?</font>

345
00:22:44,230 --> 00:22:46,000
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Let me prove it to you.</font>

346
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:48,850
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Anna, light this candle for me.</font>

347
00:22:48,850 --> 00:22:50,180
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Oh, sure.</font>

348
00:22:55,170 --> 00:22:57,440
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">If I cover it with this glass jar,</font>

349
00:22:57,440 --> 00:22:59,430
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">do you know what will happen?</font>

350
00:22:59,430 --> 00:23:02,750
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Um, the flame will go out.</font>

351
00:23:03,250 --> 00:23:05,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And why will the flame go out?</font>

352
00:23:05,930 --> 00:23:08,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Because the air inside the jar is used up.</font>

353
00:23:09,910 --> 00:23:13,000
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You mean, because there's 
no air left in the jar,</font>

354
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:14,420
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">that's why the flame goes out?</font>

355
00:23:14,420 --> 00:23:15,820
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yes, Your Highness.</font>

356
00:23:15,820 --> 00:23:19,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Nana, pour that limewater 
over there into this basin.</font>

357
00:23:19,530 --> 00:23:21,430
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Oh! Okay.</font>

358
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:27,230
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Now, let's take a look.</font>

359
00:23:27,230 --> 00:23:30,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">If I lift this jar, 
what do you think will happen?</font>

360
00:23:36,930 --> 00:23:38,610
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Ah! This is...</font>

361
00:23:38,610 --> 00:23:40,410
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">If there was nothing in the jar,</font>

362
00:23:40,410 --> 00:23:42,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">we wouldn't see bubbles or 
changes in the water surface.</font>

363
00:23:42,350 --> 00:23:45,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">This proves that air contains 
at least two different gases.</font>

364
00:23:45,840 --> 00:23:49,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">In fact, the candle only consumes 
a part of the air as it burns.</font>

365
00:23:49,740 --> 00:23:52,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The other part cannot 
participate in combustion,</font>

366
00:23:52,350 --> 00:23:54,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and also turns the limewater cloudy.</font>

367
00:23:54,140 --> 00:23:55,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Although they're both 
colorless and odorless,</font>

368
00:23:55,840 --> 00:23:57,340
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">they have completely different properties.</font>

369
00:23:57,340 --> 00:23:59,550
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">So that's how it is.</font>

370
00:23:59,550 --> 00:24:01,040
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But what's the use of knowing all this?</font>

371
00:24:01,040 --> 00:24:03,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">If we use the first gas alone,</font>

372
00:24:03,660 --> 00:24:05,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">we can make the flame burn brighter.</font>

373
00:24:05,880 --> 00:24:07,620
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And the second type of gas</font>

374
00:24:07,620 --> 00:24:09,540
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">can extinguish the flame quickly.</font>

375
00:24:11,350 --> 00:24:12,500
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Well said.</font>

376
00:24:12,500 --> 00:24:14,360
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Ever since humans learned to use fire,</font>

377
00:24:14,360 --> 00:24:16,170
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">we've set ourselves apart from animals.</font>

378
00:24:16,170 --> 00:24:18,340
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And its origin might 
have been an accident,</font>

379
00:24:18,340 --> 00:24:20,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">perhaps lightning striking a tree,</font>

380
00:24:20,140 --> 00:24:23,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">or sparks from stones colliding 
that ignited a flame.</font>

381
00:24:23,350 --> 00:24:25,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But if no one had noticed this,</font>

382
00:24:25,530 --> 00:24:27,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">if no one had tried to harness it,</font>

383
00:24:27,270 --> 00:24:29,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">we might still be no different 
from beasts today.</font>

384
00:24:29,350 --> 00:24:31,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">This experiment is meant to show you that</font>

385
00:24:31,250 --> 00:24:34,160
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">curiosity and thinking are the 
driving forces of human progress.</font>

386
00:24:34,160 --> 00:24:37,210
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You've just been in the rain. 
Have some hot water, Your Highness.</font>

387
00:24:37,210 --> 00:24:38,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Thank you, Carter.</font>

388
00:24:38,350 --> 00:24:41,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">In fact, there are many such 
potential forces in nature</font>

389
00:24:41,270 --> 00:24:42,850
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">waiting for us to discover and use them.</font>

390
00:24:42,850 --> 00:24:45,550
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They may seem insignificant, 
but when harnessed together,</font>

391
00:24:45,550 --> 00:24:47,350
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">they can produce astonishing power.</font>

392
00:24:47,740 --> 00:24:50,700
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I believe the power of 
witches is the same.</font>

393
00:24:51,320 --> 00:24:52,860
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That's all for today's lesson.</font>

394
00:24:52,860 --> 00:24:55,380
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Carter, you're responsible 
for taking Nana back.</font>

395
00:24:55,380 --> 00:24:56,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yes, Your Highness.</font>

396
00:24:56,470 --> 00:24:57,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Goodbye, Your Highness.</font>

397
00:24:58,670 --> 00:25:01,200
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Anna, you should also 
go back and get some rest.</font>

398
00:25:01,200 --> 00:25:02,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Thank you, Your Highness.</font>

399
00:25:04,050 --> 00:25:05,670
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Oh, by the way, Carter.</font>

400
00:25:05,670 --> 00:25:06,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Did you confirm it?</font>

401
00:25:06,720 --> 00:25:08,450
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Are the Snow Powder and 
ice that I requested</font>

402
00:25:08,450 --> 00:25:10,210
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">in the shipment that arrived 
from Willow Town today?</font>

403
00:25:10,210 --> 00:25:11,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Oh, yes, Your Highness.</font>

404
00:25:11,810 --> 00:25:13,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I've already had someone check.</font>

405
00:25:13,470 --> 00:25:16,370
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But why do you need 
so much Snow Powder and ice?</font>

406
00:25:16,370 --> 00:25:18,100
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">We don't have any celebrations right now,</font>

407
00:25:18,100 --> 00:25:20,050
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">nor anything that needs to be kept cold.</font>

408
00:25:22,620 --> 00:25:24,260
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">For the next experiment.</font>

409
00:26:26,510 --> 00:26:27,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Don't move.</font>

410
00:26:30,890 --> 00:26:32,680
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">{\an8}Translator: Henry Lin
Timer: Henry Lin
Editor: Zachary Carlysle
QC: William Haggard</font>

